* Please read the following notes carefully since all the LT7171 features and programmability choices are not modelled\n \n(1) PMBus communication and memory address related functions and pins are not modeled, \nincluding SDA, SCL, WP. The pins shown in the symbol is only for representation \n(2) Changes to parameter values while the simulation is running will not take effect unless the\nsimulation is stopped and restarted. This is different from the way the part operates which will\nrespond to the changes while running.  \n(3) Resistor Configuration pins are not modelled (VOUT_CFG,ASEL, PWM_CFG). The pins shown in the symbol is only for representation \n(4) Only default fault responses are modelled. The part offers diffeent fault responses choices\n(5) Initialization time is not modelled.\n \nThe following parameters can be defined by right-clicking on the LT7171 symbol.\nThe nomenclature used here may differ from the one in the data sheet. If any value of these parameters is\nset beyond the scope described in the data sheet, the resulting simulation will not be meaningful.:\n \nFrequency_switch -- in Hz, sets switching frequency\n \nVout_range -- sets maximum output range, 0 for 1.375V, 1 for 2.75V, 2 for 5.5V\n \nVout_command -- in volt, sets output voltage\n \nTon_delay & Ton_rise -- in sec, set ON delay and soft-start time\nToff_delay & Toff_fall -- in sec, set OFF delay and soft-off time \n \nIlim_range -- sets current limit options:\n   0 positive valley current limit of 9A per phase, negative valley current limit of -6A\n   1 positive valley current limit of 13A per phase, negative valley current limit of -7.6A\n   2 positive valley current limit of 15.6A per phase, negative valley current limit of -9.4A\n   3 positive valley current limit of 21.4A per phase, negative valley current limit of -12A         \n \n \n     \nGMEA_control--Sets Error Amp parameters, N=0 to 31\n     GmEA = 0.15mS*(n+1)/(2^VOUT_RANGE)   (relative to VSENSE inputs)\n     \n \nRITH--in ohm, programmable internal compensation\n \nCITH--in Farad, programmable internal compensation\n \n \nMFR_PWM_PHASE-- in degree, sets the SW0 phase delay in 15-degree increments with respect to the SYNC frequency if present.\n \n \n \nVout_UV_Fault_Limit and Vout_OV_Fault_Limit --- in volt, set the undervoltage and overvoltage fault limit.\nVout_UV_Warn_Limit and Vout_OV_Warn_Limit-- in volt, set the undervoltage and overvoltage warning limit.\n \n \nMFR_DISCHARGE_THRESHOLD--Output voltage threshold to determine that the output has decayed sufficiently to enable the channel\n \nMFR_RETRY_DELAY -- sets the time in milliseconds to retry the LT7171_verify_2025JAN09 after shuts down due to a fault\n \nEN_SYNC_OUT ---1 Output SYNC Pulses, 0 SYNC works as input.\n \nTON_MAX_FAULT_LIMIT--  Determines how long the LT7171 can attempt to soft-start the output without reaching the output undervoltage fault limit.\n \nTo simulate Polyphase load-sharing operation \n \nTie RUN, VIN, SHARE_CLK, _FAULT, _ALERT, PGOOD, ITH pins of all the parts together\nset EN_SYNC_OUT = 1 for only one part and set EN_SYNC_OUT = 0 for all other parts\nThe parameters set in both the part should be identical other than EN_SYNC_OUT
.lib LT7171.sub
